---
import { Code } from "astro-expressive-code/components"
---

<section>
  <h2 id="theming">Theming</h2>
  <p>
    The basic idea is to define one source color, <code>--palette-source</code>,
    and then derive the rest of the 16-step palette from it.
  </p>

  <Code
    code={`:where(html) {
  --palette-source: oklch(0.58 0.18 264);
  --palette-hue-rotate-by: 0;
}`}
    lang="css"
  />

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Must be <code>oklch()</code>. </strong>
      <li>
        <strong><code>--palette-hue-rotate-by</code></strong> is a separate knob for
        per-step warm/cool drift, in degrees.
      </li>
    </li>

    <p>
      You can override the source color anywhere you want for useful or cool
      effect:
    </p>

    <Code
      code={`:where(.ui-warning) {
  --palette-source: oklch(0.58 0.21 var(--hue-orange));
}`}
      lang="css"
    />
  </ul>

  <section>
    <h2 id="motion">Motion</h2>
    <p>
      Use the <code>--motion</code> variable to turn motion on or off. The default
      value is <code>1</code>. If a user has <code
        >prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code
      > enabled,
      <code>--motion</code> will be set to <code>0</code> by default.
    </p>

    <h3 id="motion-global">Global Classes</h3>
    <p>
      Adding these utility classes to the <code>html</code> element will override
      the OS preference.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <code>.ui-motion-off</code>: sets <code>--motion: 0</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <code>.ui-motion-on</code>: sets <code>--motion: 1</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        <code>.ui-motion-debug</code>: sets <code>--motion: 10</code> (slows down
        transitions 10x).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <Code code={`<html lang="en" class="ui-motion-debug">`} lang="html" />

    <h3 id="motion-local">Local Overrides</h3>
    <p>
      Components use a local <code>--_motion</code> variable that allows you to disable
      motion for each component individually if you want.
    </p>
    <Code
      code={`<button class="ui-button" style="--_motion: 0">
  Instant interaction
</button>`}
      lang="html"
    />

    <p>
      Additionally, this is how you could include <code>--motion</code> in your CSS:
    </p>
    <Code
      code={`transition: transform calc(0.2s * var(--motion, 1)) ease;`}
      lang="css"
    />
  </section>
</section>
